!!! Implementation

!!!! procedure

    Voting with integer weight $n$ on a bill costs ${n \choose 2}$ points.  No
    senator may spend more than $N=100$ points during any term.  A bill passes
    in the Senate if and only if it receives strictly more than $11/20$ths of
    the unweighted vote and strictly more than $1/2$ of the weighted vote.

    Costs will be exacted once a bill is approved by (a simple majority in) the
    House.  

